        "description": {
            "value": "<p>Many cultures of Golarion have a tattoo to turn away harm; as such, warding tattoos often resemble whichever dangers are most common to the culture, such as a wild beast or a whirlpool in the high seas of the Shackles. You gain resistance 2 to spells cast by fiends and magical attacks by fiends.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">r</span> envision</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p>\n<p><strong>Trigger</strong> An enemy, hazard, or the environment makes an attack against your AC, requires you to attempt a saving throw, or causes you to take damage automatically</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> Until the end of the current turn, against the triggering effect, you gain a +1 status bonus to AC and saving throws and gain resistance 2 to damage. Your resistance to damage from fiends and magical attacks by fiends becomes resistance 5.</p>"
        },
